00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:46.150
Accessibility is the use
of specifically for people

00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:48.090
that have disabilities.

00:08:48.090 --> 00:08:51.110
When we speak about accessibility,
we always preach that

00:08:51.110 --> 00:08:54.500
when you implement accessibility,
in essence you're allowing

00:08:54.500 --> 00:08:57.970
a more simplified
usability for your product.

00:08:57.970 --> 00:09:02.020
If you're implementing
usability, but you haven't taken

00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:05.620
into account accessibility,
then you're actually missing one part

00:09:05.620 --> 00:09:06.780
of usability.

00:09:06.780 --> 00:09:11.620
Therefore, I see a correlation,
and I work alongside the correlation

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:12.700
between the two.

00:09:12.700 --> 00:09:14.190
I don't separate them.

00:09:14.190 --> 00:09:16.430
Be interesting to hear from
you if there's anything

00:09:16.430 --> 00:09:18.720
that you think differently here.

00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:22.760
If I deep dive or dive a little
deeper into the definition

00:09:22.760 --> 00:09:29.290
of usability according to the W3C, it
states that usability is the extent

00:09:29.290 --> 00:09:32.160
to which a product can
be used by specific users

00:09:32.160 --> 00:09:34.559
to achieve specific
goals effectively,

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:39.180
efficiently and with satisfaction
in a specified context of use.

00:09:39.180 --> 00:09:44.740
Now if we look at the highlighted,
I have a few words here

00:09:44.740 --> 00:09:50.490
that are highlighted: specified
users, and specified context of use.

00:09:50.490 --> 00:09:54.980
If I look at those specifically
from an accessibility point of view,

00:09:54.980 --> 00:09:58.880
then specified users,
in the definition of usability

00:09:58.880 --> 00:10:02.610
from an accessibility perspective,
would include people with a range

00:10:02.610 --> 00:10:05.030
of disabilities or capabilities.

00:10:06.160 --> 00:10:09.760
Specified context of use would
include accessibility considerations

00:10:09.760 --> 00:10:12.280
such as assistive technologies.

00:10:12.280 --> 00:10:15.290
Therefore, the two go hand in
hand, as I see it.

00:10:16.580 --> 00:10:19.090
I don't feel I need
to go into the WCAG.

00:10:19.090 --> 00:10:21.680
I'm sure that everyone
here is familiar with it.

00:10:21.680 --> 00:10:24.290
If it's the first time you're
hearing of digital accessibility

00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:30.630
in my presentation here,
